<br>
Now, on topic.<br>
<br>
I am a SK.  I read the SK boards, and also visit the steel warrior at times.  I can not speak for paladins, but both SK's and warriors know that warrior aggro is broken.<br>
<br>
Can a group use a warrior as MT and not have aggro problems?  Of course they can, but it takes sacrifices. (waiting to slow, waiting to debuff, waiting to nuke)  The end result is that even though warriors are supposed to be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>the</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> tank, they are often passed up in favor of a knight for almost every situation other than defensive required mobs.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Yes, it's everyone's job to control their aggro but the thing is, with a knight tank you don't really HAVE to. You can just go balls-out offense and the knight will keep aggro anyway. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Exactly.  Why deal with having to control your aggro when you can just get a knight and not worry about it?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I have yet to meet a cleric that I have found who has said, all other things being equal, &quot;Let's take the knight instead of the warrior&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
look harder Jhary.  I find them all the time.  Unless it is a defensive required fight, or the warrior is a friend and known to be skilled and well equipped, I have yet to find a cleric who would take a warrior over a knight, all things being equal.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>when push comes to shove on a real raid<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The warrior with defensive is tanking.  I'm not stupid, or unrealistic about my tanking abilities.  But that being said it is much more than only &quot;Certain LDoN dungeons&quot; where knights are prefered.<br>
More like 90% or more of the games content.<br>
<br>
Those of you who say warriors don't need fixxed, maybe you are right.  But the perception is that they do.  The perception is that because of infailable aggro generation capabilities, knights make better tanks for most purposes.  And every time a knight tanks and the slower can slow on INC and the wizards can nuke with out worry without ever drawing a touch of aggro, the perception becomes more engrained, and more warriors sit LFG as knights are taken in their place.<br>
<br>
It is time to fix warrior taunt.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
